b'Inner Life: #ThePocketBag
.

b'The finishing touches
.
Gently brushed for softness and lustre, the cashmere is then dried, fringed and checked by hand to ensure the highest quality
.
#Burberry'

b'Woven into history 
.
Weaving takes place on complex looms, individually set up for each pattern change in a precise sequence. Once this is done, the scarves are washed in local spring water from the River Lossie, which surrounds the mill
.
#Burberry'

b'Crafted in cashmere 
.
Made at a centuries-old mill in Scotland, our cashmere scarves are dyed for up to six hours in order to create a rich and vivid colour before shades are intricately blended together 
.
#Burberry'

b'A considered approach
.
In a process that involves over 30 different steps, the cashmere is woven, washed in local spring water and carefully brushed using techniques passed down through generations
.
#Burberry'

b'A timeless icon
.
Crafted in a 200-year-old mill in the Scottish countryside, our cashmere scarves are made from the finest materials using expert methods
.
#Burberry'

b'An enduring partnership\n.\nOur cashmere scarves are an integral part of the #Burberry DNA, as is our relationship with the family-run Scottish mill who craft them \xe2\x80\x93 a partnership that started in 1900'
